\end{eqnarray}

{\noindent} and the expressions for the potential and for the electrostatic case turn to the standard case.

Considering the point charge, we can use the charge distribution at the origin, $\rho \left(\vec{r}\,'\right) = q \, \delta^3 \left(\vec{r}\,'\right)$,
